Object.Field: Copy of IKM Oracle Incremental Update (MERGE)

COMPONENT NAME: IKM Oracle Incremental Update (MERGE)
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Integration Knowledge Module - Integrates data into an Oracle (9i or above) target table in incremental update mode using the MERGE dml statement. - Inexistent rows are inserted; already existing rows are updated. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled. - When using this module with a journalized source table, it is possible to synchronize deletions.
Restrictions: - When working with journalized data, if the "Synchronize deletions from journal" is executed, the deleted rows on the target are committed - Compatible only with Oracle 9i database - Comparison of data is made using the Update Key defined in the interface. It has to be set. - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key) - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore. - Deletes are commited regardless of the COMMIT option - The option ANALYZE_TARGET will evaluate correct statictics only if COMMIT is set to Yes. Otherwise, the IKM will gather statistics based upon the old data.
Version History:
Last Update: DEC-2007 - Introduced COMPATIBLE - Use DBMS_STATS instead of analyze table - Use purge option - Introduced VALIDATE - Non-Unique index before CKM call
Commit all data inserted or updated in the target datastore.
Check this option to synchronize journalized deletions. This option will take effect only if one source table is journalized in your interface.
Check this option if you wish to perform flow control.
Check this option to recycle data rejected by flow control in a previous execution of this interface.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

Use this option to specify the attributes for the integration table at create time and used for increasing performance. This option is set by default to NOLOGGING (valid only from Oracle v8). This option may be left empty.
This option enables/disables index creation on flow table.

This option affects the use of PURGE key word and the way statistics are collected:
Values PURGE STATS 10 Yes DBMS_STATS 9 No DBMS_STATS 8 No ANALYZE

This option generates an extra validation step during development. Validations performed are: - validation of KM option COMPATIBLE - validation of RDBMS version of staging database
This option should be turned off for all production use in particular for high-frequency execution. There is not added value in production, only processing overhead.
Note : Execute this this grant as sys to modify the permissions of the target data server schema
grant select on v_$parameter to <user>;

Valid values are - MINUS: The MINUS clause uses the Minus set operator when populating the flow table. This clause is used to exclude identical records already existing in the target. - NOT_EXISTS: The NOT EXISTS clause uses the Not Exists set operator when populating the flow table. This clause is used to exclude identical records already existing in the target. - POST_FLOW: all records from source are loaded into flow table. After that an update statement is used to flag all rows in flow table, which identically exist in target. - NONE: all records from source are loaded into flow table. All target records are updated even when target records is identical to flow table record.
Check this option if you wish to analyze the target table before loading data into the integration table.
Use this option to specify the hint to be used while loading the integration table.
Disable/enable constraints before/after the data is loaded into target table
None, Disable, Enable, Disable and Enable
Select the appropriate value to disable/enable constraints before/after the data is loaded into target table
Disable/enable indexes before/after the data is loaded into target table
None, Disable, Enable, Enable Rebuild Online, Disable and Enable, Disable and Enable Rebuild Online
Select the appropriate value to disable/enable indexes before/after the data is loaded into target table

<% if (odiRef.getOption("CONSTRAINTS").equals("Disable") || odiRef.getOption("CONSTRAINTS").equals("Disable and Enable")) { %>

connection = odiRef.getJDBCConnection( "DEST" )
selConsQuery = "select constraint_name from all_constraints where owner = '<%= odiRef.getSchemaName() %>' and table_name = '<%= odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_NAME") %>' and status = 'ENABLED'"

try {
  selConsStmt = connection.createStatement();
  selConsResultSet = selConsStmt.executeQuery(selConsQuery);
  alterStmt = connection.createStatement()

  while (selConsResultSet.next()) {
     alterSql = "alter table <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> disable constraint "+selConsResultSet.getString("constraint_name")
     odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "Executing the statement : " + alterSql)
     alterStmt.execute(alterSql);
  }
} finally {
  if (alterStmt != null) { try { alterStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selConsResultSet != null) { try { selConsResultSet.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selConsStmt != null) { try { selConsStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }  
}

<%}%>

<% String indexes = odiRef.getOption("INDEXES");
if (indexes.equals("Disable") || indexes.equals("Disable and Enable") || indexes.equals("Disable and Enable Rebuild Online")) { 
%>

connection = odiRef.getJDBCConnection( "DEST" )
selIdxQuery = "select index_name from all_indexes where table_owner = '<%= odiRef.getSchemaName() %>' and table_name = '<%= odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_NAME") %>' and status='VALID'"

try {
  selIdxStmt = connection.createStatement();
  selIdxResultSet = selIdxStmt.executeQuery(selIdxQuery);
  alterStmt = connection.createStatement()

  while (selIdxResultSet.next()) {
     alterSql = "alter index <%= odiRef.getSchemaName() %>."+selIdxResultSet.getString("index_name")+" unusable"
     odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "Executing the statement : " + alterSql)
     alterStmt.execute(alterSql);
  }
  alterSql = "alter session set SKIP_UNUSABLE_INDEXES = true";
  odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "Executing the statement : " + alterSql)
  alterStmt.execute(alterSql);
} finally {
  if (alterStmt != null) { try { alterStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selIdxResultSet != null) { try { selIdxResultSet.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selIdxStmt != null) { try { selIdxStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }  
}

<%}%>

<% if (odiRef.getOption("CONSTRAINTS").equals("Enable") || odiRef.getOption("CONSTRAINTS").equals("Disable and Enable")) { %>

connection = odiRef.getJDBCConnection( "DEST" )
selConsQuery = "select constraint_name from all_constraints where owner = '<%= odiRef.getSchemaName() %>' and table_name = '<%= odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_NAME") %>' and status = 'DISABLED'"
try {
  selConsStmt = connection.createStatement()
  selConsResultSet = selConsStmt.executeQuery(selConsQuery) 

  alterStmt = connection.createStatement();
  
  exception = null
  strBuilder = null
  while (selConsResultSet.next()) {
    try {
      alterSql = "alter table <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> enable constraint "+selConsResultSet.getString("constraint_name")
      odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "Executing the statement : " + alterSql)
      alterStmt.execute(alterSql)
    } catch (java.sql.SQLException e) {
      if (exception == null) {
        strBuilder = new StringBuilder(System.getProperty("line.separator"))
        exception = e
      }
      strBuilder.append(e.getMessage())
      odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.SEVERE, "Executing the statement '"+alterSql+"' failed."+e.getMessage())
    }
  }
  
  if (exception != null) {
    odiEx = new OdiKMException("ODIKM-ORA-10005", "ODIKM-ORA-10005: Enabling constraints failed. {0} ", strBuilder.toString())
    odiEx.addSuppressed(exception)
    throw odiEx
  }   
  
} finally {
  if (alterStmt != null) { try { alterStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selConsResultSet != null) { try { selConsResultSet.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selConsStmt != null) { try { selConsStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
}

<%}%>

try {
  selIdxStmt = connection.createStatement();

} finally {
  if (alterStmt != null) { try { alterStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selIdxResultSet != null) { try { selIdxResultSet.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selIdxStmt != null) { try { selIdxStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }  
}
